The given condition is an equation. To find the value of $x$ that satisfies this equation, we follow hint 1: multiply the first term by 3 and the second term by 2 and then subtract the resulting expressions:

\begin{align*}
  3\left(\dfrac{x}{2}\right) - 2\left(\dfrac{x}{3}\right) &= 5 \\
  x - x/3 &= 30 \\
  x\left(1-\dfrac{2}{3}\right) &= 30 \\
  x &= \dfrac{90}{11} \\
  x &\approx 8.18181818\text{ (rounded to 10 decimal places)}
\end{align*}

Since we cannot obtain exact numerical answers using a calculator, we approximate the value of $x$ rounded to 10 decimal places.

The answer is: $x\approx 8.18181818$.
